What separates a good laptop from a great one is how it balances power, efficiency, portability, and comfort.
Increasingly, it should have a touchscreen to provide more flexibility with how you are able to interact with the laptop.
Naming “the best laptop” is a little different than naming the best phone or tablet.
The best laptop right now: HP Spectre x360 13If you’re looking for a straightforward, compact, well-performing laptop with a good keyboard and trackpad, our recommendation is HP’s latest Spectre x360 13.
Overall, the Spectre x360 13 hits the right balance of features, performance, design, and cost better than any other laptop option right now, earning it our recommendation.